<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-05-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-05-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="396" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d396">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Meyer</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-05-21"><hi rend="italic">May 21,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Meyer states that the British consul has reported to him that
                            Stuart, American vice-consul at Batum, was murdered last night, and that
                            the murderers are unknown.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>